mpute every future position exactly)\nGate A at (6,3): open exactly when (t mod 6) is in {0, 1, 2}. So it is open at t=0,1,2,6,7,8,... and closed at t=3,4,5,9,10,11,... You can only step ONTO it at a tick t+1 where it is open.\nGate B at (7,4): open exactly when (t mod 6) is in {0, 1, 5}. So it is open at t=0,1,5,6,7,11,... and closed at t=2,3,4,8,9,10,... You can only step ONTO it at a tick t+1 where it is open.\nGuard P: walks a fixed cycle of length 8. Its position at tick t is determined by (t mod 8) as follows: t mod 8=0: (3,2); t mod 8=1: (4,2); t mod 8=2: (4,1); t mod 8=3: (3,1); t mod 8=4: (2,1); t mod 8=5: (3,1); t mod 8=6: (4,1); t mod 8=7: (4,2). This repeats forever.\nGuard Q: walks a fixed cycle of length 6. Its position at tick t is determined by (t mod 6) as follows: t mod 6=0: (3,8); t mod 6=1: (3,7); t mod 6=2: (2,7); t mod 6=3: (2,8); t mod 6=4: (2,7); t mod 6=5: (3,7). This repeats forever.\n\nYOUR JOB\nParcel 1: pick it up at (6,8) (map glyph '1'), deliver it to (9,4) (map glyph 'x'). Pickup and delivery happen automatically when you end a tick on the cell.\nParcel 2: pick it up at (4,6) (map glyph '2'), deliver it to (3,9) (map glyph 'y'). Pickup and delivery happen automatically when you end a tick on the cell.\nDeliver every parcel within 40 ticks. You move by committing to plans of\nexactly 5 moves at a time; you have at most 8 plans in total.\nIf you deliver the last parcel mid-plan, the game ends immediately and the unused\nmoves are discarded.\n\nWORKED EXAMPLE (for the rules only - this is NOT the map above): suppose you stand at\n(2,2), gate G at (3,2) has period 2 and is open when (t mod 2) = 1, and it is now t=0.\nMoving E now (arriving at t=1, when the gate is open) succeeds. But moving E at t=1\n(arriving at t=2, when the gate is closed) is a BUMP: you stay at (2,2) and tick 2 is\nwasted. The right play at t=1 is to WAIT once and then move E, arriving at t=3 when\nthe gate is open again.\n\nAfter each plan you receive a per-tick log 